      , a tool I built.
    </p>
    <p>
      This email contains a tracking pixel, a tiny invisible image. Opening it did more than reveal that you&#x27;d opened the email; it also gave away some information about you and your device.
    </p>
    <p>
      Some email providers block pixels like this one. If yours didn&#x27;t, opening this email should have already triggered a second one, which shows you everything the pixel gathered.
    </p>
    <p>
